"(1) (i) The hum of recycled air thrummed through the steel corridors of , a low, steady pulse that mingled with the distant whir of automated systems. Henry’s breath fogged the cold glass of his observation window as he watched the orange security lights flicker in the sublevel bays.\n(2) Outside, the Martian dust glimmered under the base’s artificial sun, but inside, tension crackled like static. (ii) On the monitor before him, the cryo-pods lined up like sleeping giants, their transparent shells shimmering with internal diagnostics.\n(3) Each pod’s status was supposed to be unassailable, but today, something felt wrong. March 23, 2224. witnessed a cryo-pod integrity breach.\n(4) The faintest stutter in the status readouts made Henry’s pulse tighten, though he tried to attribute it to the usual system lag.\n(5) (iii) At precisely 14:32 hours on , the alert blared through the comms—“Cryo Pod 7B integrity breach detected.” Henry’s fingers flew to the console, his mind racing through training manuals and protocol, but the numbers on the screen betrayed a reality he had only seen in simulation.\n(6) (iv) He watched as pressure sensors flashed red along the outer shell of Pod 7B. Henry Reed.\n(7) The once-smooth surface rippled, a thin fissure spreading beneath the transparent armor.\n(8) Alarms flashed in neon streaks across the ceiling, and the base’s PA system screamed warnings in a shrill, synthetic voice. Phobos Military Base.\n(9) Henry’s throat constricted;"